06211nam a22009615i 9781463242541DE-B159720220110023848.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220110t20212021nju    fo  d z      eng d  a2020056103  a97814632425417 a10.31826/97814632425412doi  a(DE-B1597)579346  a(OCoLC)1243311470  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anjucUS-NJ00aBL1060b.P76 1913 4aBL1060b.P76 1913 7aREL0250002bisacsh04a305.6095422300aTowards a Culture of Co-Existence in Pluralistic Societies :bThe Middle East and India /ced. by Dietmar Winkler. 1aPiscataway, NJ : bGorgias Press, c[2021] 4c©2021  a1 online resource (266 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aPro Oriente Studies in the Syriac Tradition ;v40 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe present volume focusses on a culture of co-existence in pluralistic societies in the Middle East and in India. The topic is approached from various different angles. Pro Oriente might not be able to contribute to immediate peace-making, which has to be a political task, but may contribute substantially to peace-keeping, to support a peaceful co-existence by developing ideas, prospects, and chances for peace. Reflecting on achievements, developing perspectives and visions for the future, not only in theory but also in practice, giving political impulses, and lobbying for a peaceful living together is the very task of Pro Oriente. Contributions come from Archbishops Paul Matar, Mor Theophilose Kuriakose, Joseph Powathil and Paul Nabil El-Sayah, Bishop Mar Antoine Audo SJ, Frans Bouwen MAfr, Philip Nelpuraparambil, Sidney H. Griffith, Herman Theule, Berge Traboulsi, Baby Varghese and Dietmar W. Winkler. Forewords are given by Cardinal-Patriarch Louis Raphael I. Sako, Cardinal Kurt Koch, Cardinal Christoph Schönborn and Pro Oriente President Alfons M. Kloss. In a special section, the post-synodical Exhortation on the Middle East Synod “Ecclesia in Medio Oriente” by Pope Benedict XVI is published. The present book is dedicated to Metropolitan Mar Joseph Powathil, who has contributed substantially to the unofficial Pro Oriente dialogue within the Churches of Syriac tradition from its beginnings, on the occasion of his 90th birthday.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aReligious pluralismzIndiavCongresses. 0aReligious pluralismzMiddle EastvCongresses. 4aEcumenism. 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Ecumenism & Interfaith.2bisacsh1 aAudo, Mar Antoine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenedict, Pope, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBouwen, Frans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffith, Sidney H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuriakose, Mar Teophilose, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatar, Mar Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNabil El-Sayah, Archbishop Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNelpuraparambil, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPowathil, Mar Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTeule, Herman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrabousli, Berge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVarghese, Baby, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWinkler, Dietmar W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWinkler, Dietmar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitl